From: Ravindra Singh Budgurjar <ravindra@budgurjar.org>
Subject: [PATCH] Gate tests and bundled googletest behind a BUILD_TESTS option

OWL's CMakeLists.txt unconditionally adds the googletest subdirectory and
the tests/ target. End users building OWL just to get the daemon do not
need either, and the bundled googletest version fails to compile under
GCC 14+ with:

    error: 'dummy' may be used uninitialized [-Werror=maybe-uninitialized]

at googletest/googletest/src/gtest-death-test.cc:1301. The fix in
upstream googletest is to mark `dummy` as deliberately uninitialized,
but the version vendored here predates that fix and rebasing the
submodule is out of scope for this patch.

This change introduces `-DBUILD_TESTS=ON` (default OFF) so that:
  - end-user builds (`cmake .. && make`) succeed on GCC 14+,
  - the existing test workflow (`cmake -DBUILD_TESTS=ON ..`) is
    preserved for developers who want it.

No other behavior changes.

Signed-off-by: Ravindra Singh Budgurjar <ravindra@budgurjar.org>
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 8 +++++---
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -13,7 +13,9 @@ add_subdirectory(src)

 add_subdirectory(daemon)

-option(INSTALL_GTEST "" OFF)
-add_subdirectory(googletest)
-
-add_subdirectory(tests)
+option(BUILD_TESTS "Build the unit tests (requires a working bundled googletest)" OFF)
+if(BUILD_TESTS)
+    option(INSTALL_GTEST "" OFF)
+    add_subdirectory(googletest)
+    add_subdirectory(tests)
+endif()
